The Lagos State Government has activated an incident command structure to monitor report and make daily important decisions on the evolving trends of the coronavirus into the state. Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu, while activating the structure yesterday, said the centre was conceived after the declaration of the disease as a public health emergency by the World Health Organization . “I will take charge as the Chief Incident Commander for this concern because it is a level in which I have to get involved personally and the Commissioner for Heath will be the Deputy Incident Commander with immediate effect,” said the governor.  Collapsed market stall kills man in Umuahia Police unaware of gov’s son’s auto crash-Spokesman IGP says extra-judicial killings by policemen unacceptable